<h2>Import Accessories</h2>

<p><b>Important:</b></p>
<ol>
  <li>The file must be saved from Microsoft Excel as a tab-delimited text file.</li>
  <li>Remove the first line of column headings from the file.</li>
  <li>The document must contain <b>all</b> the columns listed below, any other columns will be ignored.</li>
  <li>The columns <b>must</b> be in this exact order.</li>
</ol>

<p><b>Columns:</b>
  accessory, model_reference, excluded, vat, included
</p>

<p>
<b>Example (We have used '|' to indicate the separation between columns.):</b><br>
</p>

<p>TWO COAT METALLIC BODY COLOUR | M080S01 | R125,201.75 | R17,528.25 | R142,730.00</p>

<% form_tag( { :action => 'import_accessories' }, { :method => :post, :multipart => true } ) do %>
	<p>
		Vehicle: <%= select_tag :new_vehicle_id, new_vehicle_options(params[:new_vehicle_id]) %>
	</p>
	<p>
		File: <%= file_field_tag :file  %>
	</p>
	<%= submit_tag 'Import'   %>
<% end %>